## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: FastAPI 0.115+
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 17 with SQLAlchemy 2.0 (async)
- **Migrations**: Alembic
- **Cache**: Redis 7
- **Package Manager**: uv
- **Testing**: pytest + pytest-asyncio + httpx
- **Formatting**: ruff

## Project Structure

- `app/` - Application package
- `app/main.py` - FastAPI application entry point
- `app/api/v1/` - API route handlers (versioned)
- `app/core/config.py` - Application settings (pydantic-settings)
- `app/db/` - Database session and base model
- `app/models/` - SQLAlchemy ORM models
- `app/schemas/` - Pydantic request/response schemas
- `app/services/` - Business logic layer
- `alembic/` - Database migrations
- `tests/` - Test suite
- `docs/supporting/` - Supporting documentation

## Development Commands

```bash
make start       # Start Docker Compose stack
make stop        # Stop all services
make bash        # Shell into web container
make shell       # Python interactive shell
make test        # Run pytest suite
make migrate     # Run Alembic migrations
make migration   # Create new migration (MSG="description")
make lint        # Run ruff linter
make format      # Auto-format with ruff
make reqs        # Compile requirements
```

## Conventions

- Use UUID primary keys for models exposed in API responses
- API versioning via `/api/v1/` prefix
- Pydantic schemas for all request/response models
- Async database operations with SQLAlchemy 2.0
- Business logic in `services/`, not in route handlers
- Tests go in `tests/` directory, not next to source files
- Use `ruff` for code formatting
- Use type hints everywhere
